I"H<h1 id="pontifications">Pontifications</h1>

<ul>
  <li>Blown out of the water by Gene Kim: <a href="https://itrevolution.com/love-letter-to-clojure-part-1/">Love Letter To Clojure (Part 1)</a> &lt;– READ THE WHOLE THING!</li>
  <li>I too didn’t realize that the “chevron” operator, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;&lt;</code> mutates the string!</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-ruby highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s2">"hello"</span> 
<span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="s2">"hello"</span> 
<span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="s2">"*"</span> 
<span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="s2">"hello*"</span> 	<span class="c1"># s value was mutated!!!!</span>
<span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s2">"hello"</span> 
<span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="kp">false</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
